Nathan Hughes was sent off and banned for three weeks following the incident on March 27 . 
  Wasps No 8 collided with George North's head as he scored a try for Northampton . 
  Hughes was initially suspended for three matches but the ban has been overturned on appeal . 
  North was left unconscious after the incident at Franklin's Gardens . 
  The Wales winger was knocked out for the third time in two months . 
 